THE suspect in Jabulile Nkosi’s murder case is behind bars. Brigadier Mathapelo Peters said on Sunday afternoon, Alexandra police were driving along East Bank Avenue near Jukskei Park, when residents alerted them about spotting a woman’s body. “Police found the body of a woman who was shot in the upper body and she was subsequently certified dead on the scene by paramedics. A murder case was immediately registered for investigation.” Peters also told Daily Sun on Tuesday, a priority investigation kicked off and a possible suspect was taken in for questioning. “Preliminary evidence linked the 25-year old taxi driver to the murder and he was immediately arrested.” She said the suspect appeared in Alexandra Magistrates Court on Thursday and the case was postponed by a week for further investigation. The suspect remains in custody.